<dl id="n12080f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12080f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12080f"> 80(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> by Arthur mortally / wounded (treachery / of Mordred)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mordred, uni aux Saxons contre notre roi, causa sa chute et celle de notre pays &hellip; O! que de larmes vers&egrave;rent les m&egrave;res le lendemain de la bataille o&ugrave; notre roi tomba bless&eacute; mortellement! <br><font color="green">[Mordred, united with the Saxons against our king, caused his fall and that of our land. O, the terrible slaughter! Oh, how many motherly tears were shed the day after the battle when our king fell mortally wounded!]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 131</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
